The paper presents a novel neural network algorithm that generalizes the Rectified Linear Unit (ReLU) nonlinearity to tensor-valued hidden units. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions that the TS network can be used for image classification tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the training methods for the TS network, which suggests that it may belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions that the TS network avoids the vanishing gradient problem, which suggests that it may also belong to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) sub-category.
